page.title: 21Tricorn updated
page.content:
There have been many changes in Portsmouth since 1984, new roads, new buildings, new people but one of the biggest changes was the removal of the 3rd most ugly building in Europe! The Tricorn Centre, once a prize winning piece of architecture but never finished in the way it was planned is no more, is now an open are car park. The new Portsmouth flagship is Spinnaker Tower, a striking building late for the millennium but now there for all to see for miles around.
